HEADWORD: free-and-easy
<hw>free-and-easy</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>unconstrained
and informal; <as>as, an informal <ex>free-and-easy</ex> manner</as>.
Opposite of <ant>stiff</ant>, <ant>starchy</ant>,
<ant>formal</ant>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> casual.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>lacking normal concern for propriety.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> free-and-easy.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

